    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down.</hi> | Beckenham | <hi rend="print">Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Ap. 8 1871</date>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Mr Darwin presents his compliments to the Secretary of the Royal Academy &amp; is much obliged for the honour of the invitation for the Anniversary dinner;<ref target="#foot.f1"/> which honour he is obliged to decline on account of the state of his health.</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">CD may refer to the banquet held by the <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4100.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Royal Academy</ref> of Arts on 29 April 1871 to inaugurate the opening of that year’s Exhibition (<hi rend="italic">The Times</hi>, 1 May 1871, p. 6). CD’s invitation has not been found.</note>
        </div>        
            
